Event.0: King Athelstan of the West Saxons became the first king to rule all of England.
Event.1: Romulus Augustulus, last Western Roman Emperor, abdicates after forces led by Odoacer invade Rome. Traditional end of the Western Roman Empire
Event.2: Mother Teresa, founder of the Order of the Missionaries of Charity and winner of the 1979 Nobel Prize for Peace, was canonized by Pope Francis I.
Event.3: American entertainer Joan Rivers—who first gained fame in the 1960s as a nightclub and television comic known for the catchphrase “Can we talk?” and who later critiqued celebrities' wardrobes—died in New York City.
Event.4: Australian wildlife conservationist and television personality Steve Irwin, who achieved worldwide fame as the exuberant and risk-taking host of The Crocodile Hunter (1992–2006) TV series and related documentaries, was killed by a venomous bull stingray.
Event.5: American singer Kelly Clarkson became the first winner of the reality television series American Idol.
Event.6: The American search engine company Google Inc. was formally established as founders Sergey Brin and Larry Page filed incorporation papers.
Event.7: The National Aeronautics and Space Administration (NASA) and the U.S. Air Force launched the last Titan III rocket.
Event.8: Actor Kevin Bacon marries actress Kyra Sedgwick
Event.9: American singer-songwriter and actress Beyoncé—who achieved fame in the late 1990s as the lead singer of the R&B group Destiny's Child and then launched a successful solo career—was born.
Event.11: American swimmer Mark Spitz won his seventh gold medal during the Munich Olympic Games, the first person ever to do so in a single Olympics.
Event.12: US 4 x 100m medley relay team of Mike Stamm, Tom Bruce, Mark Spitz & Jerry Heidenreich sets world record 3:48.16 to win gold at the Munich Olympics; Mark Spitz becomes 1st athlete to win 7 Olympic gold medals at a single Games
Event.13: Beatles' single "Help!" goes #1 & stays #1 for 3 weeks
Event.14: The Ford Motor Company introduced the Edsel automobile, which was perhaps its most notable failure.
Event.15: "Swing Time", directed by George Stevens, starring Fred Astaire and Ginger Rogers, is released
Event.16: Supreme Court Justice Thurgood Marshall (21) weds Vivien Burey at First African Baptist Church in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania
